# Lumen Coding Conventions

## No TransformerEngine (TE) replacement language

Lumen is a standalone project. Do NOT describe Lumen modules as "drop-in replacements" for TransformerEngine or reference TE classes in docstrings/comments.

```python
# BAD
"""Drop-in replacement for TE's ``TEColumnParallelLinear``."""
"""Mirrors ``TESpecProvider`` — returns Lumen classes instead of TE classes."""
# Matches TE convention: ...

# GOOD
"""Column-parallel linear using Lumen GEMM."""
"""Provides Lumen module classes for Megatron-Core layer specs."""
# Formula: ...
```

Exceptions: actual code that references TE class names (e.g. `TEGroupedMLP` in imports or runtime logic) is fine — only remove TE references from documentation and comments.
